1028. ἆμέρσας βίον. Since ἆμέρδειν governs two accusativa, we may supply Πολύδωρον as the acc. of the person, and translate: “ because you deprived Polydorus of life.'’ Or ἀμέρσας may be taken in a middle sense with the acc. of the thing alone, and the meaning be simply: “ having lost thy life.''
